<Layout title="Privacy Policy | Volmer.es">
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 text-gray-300">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold mb-8 text-white">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="space-y-8 leading-relaxed">
            <section>
                <p class="text-lg">
                    Welcome to <strong>Volmer.es</strong>. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect the personal information you may provide through this website.
                </p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Last updated: January 16, 2026</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-4">1. Data Controller</h2>
                <p>
                    The data controller for the data collected on this website is <strong>Juan Bautista</strong> (hereinafter, "the Owner"). You can contact us via email at: <a href="mailto:juanbautista.dev@volmer.es" class="text-neon-pink hover:underline">juanbautista.dev@volmer.es</a>.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-4">2. Collected Data</h2>
                <p>
                    This website is primarily a personal portfolio and does not require user registration. However, we may collect data in the following circumstances:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Contact Forms:</strong> If you use the contact form or email buttons, we will receive your email address, name, and any other information you choose to include in your message.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cookies and Technical Data:</strong> We may use essential technical cookies for the website's operation and anonymous analysis tools to understand how visitors interact with the portfolio.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-4">3. Purpose of Processing</h2>
                <p>We use your personal data solely to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4 space-y-2">
                    <li>Respond to your inquiries, quote requests, or professional proposals sent through the contact methods.</li>
                    <li>Maintain the security and proper functioning of the website.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

             <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-4">4. Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>
                    We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for commercial purposes. We will only share data if we are legally legally required to do so.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-4">5. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>
                    You have the right to access, rectify, delete, limit, or object to the processing of your personal data. To exercise these rights, please send a request to the email address indicated above.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-4">6. External Links</h2>
                <p>
                    This website may contain links to other sites (such as LinkedIn, GitHub, or external projects). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of such sites. We recommend reading their privacy policies.
                </p>
            </section>
             <section class="border-t border-white/10 pt-8 mt-12">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                    If you have specific questions about this policy, do not hesitate to contact me.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
